parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the trailer brake system can cause a false warning light to appear on the dashboard, potentially distracting the driver and leading to a loss of confidence in the vehicle's safety features.
symptoms: The "Trailer Brake" warning light suddenly appears on the dashboard
even when the vehicle is not towing a trailer with its own braking system.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear view camera system can reduce the driver's visibility while reversing, increasing the risk of accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The rear view camera display shows striped
blurry lines
then turns to a blue screen with a "Service Rear Vision System" message.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The overheating and explosion of the auxiliary battery can cause damage to surrounding components, potentially leading to a loss of vehicle functionality and increasing the risk of a fire.
symptoms: The auxiliary battery explodes while the vehicle is in operation
causing damage to nearby components such as the headlight
hood insulation
windshield washer reservoir
and terminal covers.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electronic power steering system can cause the steering wheel to become firm or difficult to turn, increasing the risk of accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The steering wheel becomes firm or difficult to turn
the power steering warning light illuminates on the dashboard
the vehicle is difficult to steer
the steering wheel locks suddenly
the vehicle accelerates forward unexpectedly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the steering assist system can cause the vehicle to lose power steering, making it difficult to steer, and increasing the risk of accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The steering assist error message appears on the dashboard
the vehicle loses power steering
the steering wheel becomes difficult to turn
the vehicle is difficult to steer.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electronic rack and pinion can cause the steering wheel to become firm or difficult to turn, increasing the risk of accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The steering wheel becomes firm or difficult to turn
the power steering warning light illuminates on the dashboard
the vehicle is difficult to steer.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to lose power and speed, leading to a potential accident or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle suddenly drops to a lower gear
the vehicle is unable to accelerate
the vehicle stays in first gear
the check engine light illuminates
the vehicle loses power and speed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The strong smell of fumes when turning on the AC or vent system can be a sign of a serious safety issue, potentially causing health problems or even a fire.
symptoms: Strong smell of fumes when turning on the AC or vent system
unusual odors coming from the vents.
